sequenceDiagram
    participant RefClock as Reference Clock (Stratum 0)
    participant NTPServer as NTP Server (Stratum 1)
    participant Client as NTP Client

    RefClock-->>NTPServer: Continuous time signal\n(GPS / atomic clock)
    Note over NTPServer: Synchronized to UTC

    Note over Client: Record T1 = client send time
    Client->>NTPServer: NTP Request (UDP port 123)\nOriginTimestamp=T1

    Note over NTPServer: Record T2 = server receive time
    Note over NTPServer: Process request
    Note over NTPServer: Record T3 = server send time

    NTPServer-->>Client: NTP Response\nOriginTimestamp=T1\nReceiveTimestamp=T2\nTransmitTimestamp=T3

    Note over Client: Record T4 = client receive time
    Note over Client: Round-trip delay = (T4-T1)-(T3-T2)
    Note over Client: Clock offset = ((T2-T1)+(T3-T4))/2
    Note over Client: Adjust local clock gradually (slew)\nif offset < 128ms, else step

    Note over Client: Repeat every 64-1024 seconds\n(poll interval adapts to stability)
